
Overview of noun koine

The noun koine has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. Koine -- (a Greek dialect that flourished under the Roman Empire)
2. lingua franca, interlanguage, koine -- (a common language used by speakers of different languages; "Koine is a dialect of ancient Greek that was the lingua franca of the empire of Alexander the Great and was widely spoken throughout the eastern Mediterranean area in Roman times")
